\id HAG - The Orthodox Jewish Bible
\h CHAGGAI
\toc1 Chaggai
\toc2 Chaggai
\toc3 Hag
\mt1 Chaggai
\c 1
\p 
\v 1 In the second year of Daryavesh HaMelech, in the sixth month, in yom echad of the month, came the Devar \nd Hashem\nd* by Chaggai HaNavi unto Zerubavel ben Sh'altiel, Governor of Yehudah, and to Yehoshua ben Yehotzadak,\f + \fr 1:1 \ft i.e., the namesake of Moshiach, see \xt Zech 6:11-12\xt*\f* the Kohen HaGadol, saying,
\v 2 Thus saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os: This people say, The time is not come, the time that Beis \nd Hashem\nd* should be built.
\v 3 Then came the Devar \nd Hashem\nd* by Chaggai HaNavi, saying,
\v 4 Is it time for you, O ye, to dwell in your paneled batim, and this Beis\f + \fr 1:4 \ft HaMikdash\f* lie in ruins?
\v 5 Now therefore thus saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os; Consider your ways.
\v 6 Ye have sown harbeh \add (much)\add*, and bring in me'at \add (little)\add*; ye eat, but ye have not enough; ye drink, but ye are not filled with drink; ye clothe yourselves, but there is no warming; and he that earneth wages earneth wages to put them into a purse of holes.
\p 
\v 7 Thus saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os: Consider your ways.
\v 8 Go up to the har \add (mountain)\add*, and bring etz, and build HaBeis;\f + \fr 1:8 \ft HaMikdash\f* and I will take pleasure in it, and I will be glorified, saith \nd Hashem\nd*.
\v 9 Ye looked for harbeh \add (much)\add*, and, hinei, it came to me'at \add (little)\add*; and when ye brought it home, I blew it away. Why? saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os. Because of Mine Beis\f + \fr 1:9 \ft HaMikdash\f* that is in ruins, and ye run every man for his own bais.
\v 10 Therefore the Shomayim over you is stayed from dew, and Ha'Aretz is stayed from her fruit.
\v 11 And I called for a drought upon ha'aretz, and upon the harim \add (mountains)\add*, and upon the grain, and upon the new wine, and upon the oil, and upon that which ha'adamah bringeth forth, and upon ha'adam, and upon livestock, and upon all the labor of the hands.
\p 
\v 12 Then Zerubavel ben Sh'altiel, and Yehoshua ben Yehotzadak, the Kohen HaGadol, with kol she'erit HaAm, obeyed the voice of \nd Hashem\nd* Eloheichem, and the words of Chaggai HaNavi, as \nd Hashem\nd* Eloheichem had sent him, and the people did fear before \nd Hashem\nd*.
\v 13 Then spoke Chaggai malach \nd Hashem\nd* with the message of \nd Hashem\nd* unto the people, saying, I am with you, saith \nd Hashem\nd*.
\v 14 And \nd Hashem\nd* stirred up the ruach of Zerubavel ben Sh'altiel, Governor of Yehudah, and the ruach of Yehoshua ben Yehotzadak, the Kohen HaGadol, and the ruach of kol she'erit HaAm; and they came and did work in the Beis\f + \fr 1:14 \ft HaMikdash\f* of \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os, Eloheichem,
\v 15 In the four and twentieth yom of the sixth month, in the second year of Daryavesh HaMelech.\f + \fr 1:15 \ft 520 B.C.E.\f*
\c 2
\p 
\v 1 In the seventh month, in the one and twentieth yom of the month, came the Devar \nd Hashem\nd* by Chaggai HaNavi, saying:
\v 2 Speak now to Zerubavel ben Sh'altiel, Governor of Yehudah, and to Yehoshua ben Yehotzadak, the Kohen HaGadol, and to the she'erit HaAm, saying:
\v 3 Who is left among you that saw this Beis\f + \fr 2:3 \ft Hamikdash\f* in her kavod harishon? And how do ye see it now? In comparison to it, is it not in your eyes as nothing?
\v 4 Yet now chazak \add (be strong)\add*, O Zerubavel, saith \nd Hashem\nd*; and chazak \add (be strong)\add*, O Yehoshua ben Yehotzadak, Kohen HaGadol; and chazak \add (be strong)\add*, kol Am Ha'Aretz, saith \nd Hashem\nd*, and work; for I am with you, saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os.
\v 5 According to the word that I covenanted with you when ye came out of Mitzrayim, so My Ruach\f + \fr 2:5 \ft Hakodesh\f* remaineth among you; fear ye not.
\v 6 For thus saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os: Once more, it is a little while, and I will shake HaShomayim and Ha'Aretz and the yam \add (sea)\add* and the kharavah \add (arid land)\add*;
\v 7 And I will shake kol Goyim, and the Chemdat kol HaGoyim \add (desired of all nations)\add* shall come: and I will fill this Beis with kavod, saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os.
\v 8 The kesef is Mine, and the zahav is Mine, saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os.
\v 9 The kavod of this latter Beis shall be greater than of the former, saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os: and in this place will I give shalom, saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os.
\p 
\v 10 In the four and twentieth yom of the ninth month, in the second year of Daryavesh, came the Devar \nd Hashem\nd* by Chaggai HaNavi, saying,
\v 11 Thus saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os; Ask now the kohanim concerning the torah, saying,
\v 12 If one carry basar kodesh in the fold of his garment, and with his fold do touch lechem, or that which is boiled, or yayin, or shemen \add (olive oil)\add*, or any food, shall it thus be made kodesh? And the kohanim answered and said, Lo \add (No)\add*.
\v 13 Then said Chaggai, If one that is tamei \add (unclean)\add* by a nefesh \add (dead body)\add* touch any of these, shall it be tamei? And the kohanim answered and said, It shall be tamei.
\v 14 Then answered Chaggai, and said, So is this people, and so is this nation before Me, saith \nd Hashem\nd*; and so is every work of their hands; and that which they offer there is tamei \add (unclean)\add*.
\v 15 And now, I pray you, consider from this yom and onward, from before an even \add (stone)\add* was laid upon an even \add (stone)\add* in the Heikhal \nd Hashem\nd*;
\v 16 Since those yamim were, when one came to a heap of grain of twenty measures, there were but ten; when one came to the wine vat for to draw out fifty vessels, there were but twenty.
\v 17 I struck you with blight and with mildew and with hail in all the labors of your hands; yet ye made not teshuvah to Me, saith \nd Hashem\nd*.
\v 18 Consider now from this yom and onward, from the four and twentieth yom of the ninth month, even from the yom that the Yesod \add (Foundation)\add* of the Heikhal \nd Hashem\nd* was laid, consider it.
\v 19 Is the seed still in the granary? As yet the gefen, and the [etz] te'enah, and the pomegranate, and etz hazayit \add (olive tree)\add*, hath not brought forth. From this yom forth will I bless you.
\p 
\v 20 And again the Devar \nd Hashem\nd* came unto Chaggai in the four and twentieth yom of the month, saying:
\v 21 Speak to Zerubavel, Governor of Yehudah, saying, I will shake HaShomayim and Ha'Aretz;
\v 22 And I will overthrow the throne of mamlachot \add (kingdoms)\add*, and I will destroy the chozek \add (strength)\add* of the mamlachot HaGoyim; and I will overthrow the merkavot, and those that ride in them; and the susim and their riders shall fall, every one by the cherev \add (sword)\add* of achiv.
\v 23 In that yom, saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os, will I take thee, O Zerubavel ben Sh'altiel, Avdi \add (My Servant)\add*,\f + \fr 2:23 \ft See \xt Isa 52:13\xt*\ft for this Avdi — My Servant — as a reference which is ultimately related to Moshiach\f* saith \nd Hashem\nd*, and will make thee as a chotam \add (signet ring)\add*; for I have chosen thee, saith \nd Hashem\nd* Tzva'os.
